  "local_port": 51860,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best places to visit in Dhanbad?",
  "response": "Dhanbad, often referred to as the \"Coal Capital of India,\" offers a mix of historical, cultural, and natural attractions. Here are some of the best places to visit in Dhanbad:\n\n1. **Maithon Dam**  \n   - Located about 48 km from Dhanbad, this dam is a popular tourist spot. It offers boating facilities, a beautiful view of the reservoir, and a nearby island called *Kakimath*. The *Kalyaneshwari Temple* is also nearby.\n\n2. **Panchet Dam**  \n   - Situated around 52 km from Dhanbad, this dam is another scenic location ideal for picnics and enjoying the serene surroundings.\n\n3. **Topchanchi Lake**  \n   - A man-made lake located about 37 km from Dhanbad, surrounded by hills and greenery. It\u2019s a perfect spot for relaxation and nature walks.\n\n4. **Bhatinda Falls**  \n   - Located near the Jharia coalfields, this waterfall is a hidden gem in the region and a great place to escape the hustle of the city.\n\n5. **Jharia Coal Mines**  \n   - A unique but unconventional attraction, Jharia is famous for its underground coal fires that have been burning for decades. It\u2019s an eye-opening experience to see the impact of these fires on the region.\n\n6. **Shakti Mandir**  \n   - A beautiful temple dedicated to Goddess Durga, located in the heart of Dhanbad. It\u2019s a peaceful place for spiritual seekers and those interested in local culture.\n\n7. **Lilori Sthan**  \n   - A historical site believed to be the birthplace of Goddess Sati. It\u2019s an important pilgrimage site and features a temple and a sacred pond.\n\n8. **Bioversity Park**  \n   - A botanical garden located in Dhanbad that showcases the region\u2019s flora and fauna. It\u2019s a great place for nature lovers and families.\n\n9. **Birsa Munda Park**  \n   - A well-maintained park in Dhanbad, ideal for leisurely walks, jogging, and spending time outdoors.\n\n10. **Kalyaneshwari Temple**  \n    - Located near Maithon Dam, this temple is dedicated to Goddess Kali and is a beautiful spiritual site with a peaceful ambiance.\n\nDhanbad is a city with a unique blend of industrial and natural beauty, offering a variety of experiences for visitors.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
